   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_936_1827_10_27_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Sussex-Place-24_ENK"/>24 Sussex place Regents park London
                        <date when="1827-10-27">
                     <hi rend="underline">Oct 27 1827</hi>
                  </date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>My dear Miss Edgeworth; a young bookseller of my<lb/>
                    acquaintance comes to ask an introduction to<lb/>
                    your notice &amp;, if possible, help in an annual<lb/>
                    work which he is bringing out - an annual<lb/>
                    present, to wit, for children &amp; entitled the Xmas box.<lb/>
                    He has secured the assistance of various people of real<lb/>
                    eminence &amp; I have written to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW1">Sir W. Scott</persName> &amp; <del/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SoutR1">Mr<lb/>
                        Southey</persName> to the same effect as I am now writing<lb/>
                    to you, &amp; I hope to both with prospect of favourable<lb/>
                    answer. He will of course pay very handsomely<lb/>
                    for any little tale or tale which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
                    might honour him -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>We were all rejoiced with <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BrewD1">
                  <hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Brewster's</persName> accounts<lb/>
                    of the family of Edgeworthstown town : you will I am sure<lb/>
                    be happy to hear in return that the good folks at<lb/>
                    Abbotsford are very well &amp; that my little boy<lb/>
                    has made a wonderful recovery - Believe me<lb/>
                    always very sincerely your faithful Servt<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1">J G Lockhart</persName>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p/>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
               </address>
            </closer>
